{
  "title": "AD #6 · Government in the Economy (Path B)",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "translation": "Claire 说政府应介入保护消费者，Andrew 说政府应退让让企业发展。",
      "phrases": ["Claire says", "the government should step in", "to protect consumers,", "Andrew says", "it should step aside", "so business can grow."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "我认为两种观点都跳过了让任何一方真正成立的东西。",
      "phrases": ["I think", "both views skip over", "what actually makes", "either side possible."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "政府最有用的角色是建设公共基础——道路、学校、基础研究——这些单家企业不会买单但每家企业都离不开。",
      "phrases": ["The most useful role of government", "is to build the common base —", "roads, schools,", "power grids,", "and basic research —", "that no single company", "will pay for", "but every company needs", "in order to work."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "两种观点缺了这个底座都撑不住。",
      "phrases": ["Each of the two views", "collapses", "without this base."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "保护消费者的规则只有在消费者有足够教育能读懂标签或贷款时才有效，而教育是公共的。",
      "phrases": ["Rules that protect buyers", "only help", "if buyers are educated enough", "to read a label", "or understand a loan,", "and education is public."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "商业自由也只有在道路、法庭、电力已经存在的地方才起作用，因为没有企业会自己建这些。",
      "phrases": ["Business freedom only works", "where roads, courts, and electricity", "already exist,", "since no company builds those", "by itself."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "历史把这一点说得很清楚。",
      "phrases": ["History makes the point clear."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "硅谷不是靠减少监管产生的。",
      "phrases": ["Silicon Valley", "did not come from", "less regulation."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "它来自几十年的联邦资金投入，花在斯坦福和 DARPA，产出了互联网、GPS 和晶体管。",
      "phrases": ["It came from", "decades of federal money", "spent at Stanford and DARPA", "that produced the internet,", "GPS, and the transistor."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "德国强大的中型工厂依赖部分由国家资助的 Fraunhofer 研究中心。",
      "phrases": ["Germany's strong mid-sized factories", "rely on Fraunhofer research centers", "partly paid for", "by the state."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "这些都没替代市场，而是搭起了市场表演的舞台。",
      "phrases": ["None of these", "replaced the market;", "they built the stage", "the market performs on."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "规则和自由只是小旋钮。最深的那个——影响最广的——是政府是否建起了市场自己建不了的东西。",
      "phrases": ["Rules and freedom", "are smaller knobs.", "The deepest one —", "the one with the widest reach —", "is whether the government builds", "what markets cannot build", "for themselves."]
    }
  ]
}
